  <head>
    <title>Support</title>
    <summary>DocBook technical support</summary>
    <keywords>DocBook, SourceForge, support, help</keywords>
  </head>

  <para>If you have a question about DocBook and want to know where
    you find an answer, there are several places you might check:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><ulink
          url="https://sourceforge.net/docman/display_doc.php?docid=10430&amp;group_id=21935" 
          >Five steps for finding answers to DocBook questions</ulink>
        might be a good starting point</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>one of the available DocBook <ulink
          url="http://docbook.org/wiki/moin.cgi/DocBookDiscussion"
          >discussion forums</ulink> is usually the next step</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>file a <ulink
          url="https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=373747&amp;group_id=21935&amp;func=browse" 
          >bug report</ulink> if you want to alert the DocBook Open
        Repository development team about a possible bug in the
        DocBook <ulink
          url="http://docbook.org/wiki/moin.cgi/DocBookXslStylesheets"
          >XSL</ulink> or <ulink
          url="http://docbook.org/wiki/moin.cgi/DocBookDssslStylesheets" 
          >DSSSL</ulink> Stylesheets or other release</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>file a <ulink
          url="https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=373750&amp;group_id=21935&amp;func=browse" 
          >feature request</ulink> if you instead want to request an
        enhancement to the <ulink
          url="http://docbook.org/wiki/moin.cgi/DocBookXslStylesheets"
          >XSL</ulink> or <ulink
          url="http://docbook.org/wiki/moin.cgi/DocBookDssslStylesheets" 
          >DSSSL</ulink> Stylesheets or other DocBook Open Repository
        release
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</webpage>
